place_description:
Food, coffee, wine, beer, cocktails, mocktails and more! We have something for everyone! #rendezvousatrendezbrew
Music Bingo every other Friday!

reviews_data.review_text:
Wow!!! The quality, presentation and flavors were just beautiful! It was like art on my plate and for my delectable pleasure! The quality and flavors were really just like a specialized artisan experience. The presentation was lovely!
Oh! The decor was authentic and custom! The countertops and some of the tables were exquisite!!! The custom designs were a delight to see in person!! It's absolutely gorgeous and stunning!!! Red cedar dreams for me.... The depth, warmth and polished look were a dream for me to see in person!
Isabella and the friendly owner were just too kind and felt like family instantly!
I had the pumpkin spice macchiato with espresso, non-alcoholic nojito blueberry, the lox on a cheddar bagel, the croissant with whip cream and berries and last but not least.... Bruschetta!!!!
Everything was absolutely delicious, flavorful, artistic and delectable!! High quality fresh and custom meals and beverages at Rendezbrew!!!!
Absolutely beautiful and such a treat!! I can't wait to go back pluse they have live music and the greenery is real and lively!!!
Looooooove it!!!!

We really enjoy coming here, mostly because we are the only people in the entire place.  Comfortable chairs with a relaxing vibe.  Above average cocktails, beer game is bad. The biggest issue is being understaffed.  Our group had 6 people and the last cocktail took 18 minutes to receive.  Indoor and outdoor comfortable seating available
I absolutely love the avocado toast here. The toast is great and the avocado is plenty. Thank you so much for being here Rendezvous. See you again and again and again

Such a beautiful spot with the most delicious coffee. I was so excited to meet a new real estate client and introduce them to the coffee flight. It was clean, service was amazing and coffee was AMAZING! Thank you

Latte flight, cold brew, and avocado toast?! Say less! Everything tasted amazing. Best avocado toast I've ever had. The atmosphere was great, very laid back and calming. Perfect for people of all ages. Family friendly too. Will definitely be coming back.
Just not my taste for coffee, but maybe you'll like it...

Went on a Sunday, it was busy but not overcrowded. I got an iced latte and cheddar jalapeno bagel, and both were great. The bagel was fluffy and light on the inside, and crispy on the outside, amazing! Highly recommend for a quick brunch or coffee pick me up.
I have been going here for the past 3 years now. I love their slippery sloop made with oatmilk and vegan coconut nut whip, iced. I would give 6/5 for the friendly customer service.

The owners of this place are so nice and I have never met a mean worker.  You can get coffee or a spiked drink.  Today we got the flight and it's a combination of different lattes. I really enjoyed this. The Irish coffee is delicious and this is a good place to chill out with a drink or coffee. They have tasty bagels  n the weekends. I also think the chicken salad sandwich looks delicious but I have not tried it yet.
Went as a group and the barista was great and accommodating! Had few hot cocoa and some cocktails all made on order. Was good!

Great coffee that beats the chains out there.

They have a rotating option of 3 monthly specials to try something different from the normal options out there.

I only had a machiato so I can't say much about the food or drinks. The girl working there was really nice and engaging. Plenty of seating options too. Not just in quantity but style of seating; high-top stools, chairs, sofa, etc. No music blasting, so if you need to study, you'll be able to concentrate. Restrooms were really clean too. I would definitely come back.
The service is impeccable and everyone is so friendly. You really feel at home at Rendezbrew.
Rendezbrew is always great! Great service, selection, and atmosphere! Shannon and her team are always amazing!

This is my favorite local coffee shop! Starting with excellent and friendly service, with great coffee and food, and a nice variety of seating. It's a great place for small business meetings (2-3 people) or just to chill and chat with friends.
i ordered a cold brew mocha it was watery and the chocolate tastes like hershey syrup :/
Great customer service! My coffee flight was amazing and so was my bagel. 10/10 recommend.
Incredible bagels that are fluffy on the inside and have a great crunch on the outside
They no longer serve bagels during the week. Only on weekends. Had to have my lox on a croissant. There was hardly any cream cheese on it. Won't be going back unfortunately.
I just had a coffee here, it was great but the wait time was forever. Took almost an hour to get my order.

If you're in this area and you're not stopping here to grab an avocado toast and iced coffee, you're doing it wrong. The food looks like it's out of a magazine and it's delicious. They care about the food and the people.
Great service! Good food and coffee!
Loved the atmosphere, great customer service by Alysa and the coffee !! I think We found our new favorite spot!!
The owners are amazing people. Very friendly and they engage with their community. And I love their flavor list for coffees!
My husband and I look forward to their coffee flights every month! And their cold brew is AMAZING!!!
I tried their lemonade, cider and chicken panini, everything was great. Also they have outdoor seating so you can bring your dog with you.
Best bagel I have had in the area in a while and the coffee was great too.

A friend recommended this coffee shop and I'm so glad it that I came. I ordered an iced peppermint mocha latte and it wasn't too sweet and the coffee was rich and smooth. Love all of the plants here as well! Super cute hidden gem.
Great service, great drinks, great atmosphere. I love working here.
The food, the coffee, the staff, the ambiance...all stellar.
Love their coffee flights! They're always so creative and tasty- never overly sweet which is nice. Service is always fast and friendly as well.
The bagels are awesome and the staff are super friendly.

A+++
If you love cozy coffee shops, this is for you. I would've never thought to have ordered a croissant, but we did, and it was so delicious with a cup of classic macchiato. Not too sweet and such an amazing texture, I could've easily eaten two more. The service was very friendly, making the experience even more enjoyable. Highly recommended!
Coffee, booze, charcuterie,   croissants, and bagels- all thoughtfully done. The staff was very pleasant and engaging.
This place serves amazing panini. Best coffee ever. Great customer service.
Coffee is watered down, worst chai I've ever had. Had to throw away.
Great little coffee spot tucked in the community strip mall (easy to miss). I tried the oat milk latte with honey cinnamon on top and it is delish!!
We went in the afternoon and ordered iced caramel lattes. They were perfect. Not too sweet, great espresso flavor.
Great space to work if you're able to remotely. Beverages vary from coffee to cocktails. The sandwiches......delicioso!

Stumbled across this little gem today, while needing a new environment for working from home. I spent several hours here working, and will definitely be back. The staff was very warm, the food and coffee were delicious and reasonably priced, and the atmosphere was lovely. Lots of space, very bright, and even a patio. It's easy to find with plenty of parking. I'm already looking forward to going again!

This is an anti-starbuck coffee shop and that's a good thing. The ambience is pleasant and comfortable. There are no factory made snacks or pre-brewed concoctions Everything is handmade.  I personally had one of the most flavor filled and smooth Cappuccinos this side Italy. Going back in the morning for their handmade Bagels!
Great local coffee shop, stop here all the time. Good cold brew, homemade bagels, and avocado toast. Nice atmosphere and the owners are super friendly. Recommend.

Happy I tried the daily flight. I loved that I could try three items that I was curious about. All three were excellent. We had the avocado toast and the lox bagel, and both were so delicious. I can't wait to go back!

Took my brother to drink some coffee and eat something, and we discovered that they also serve cocktails, wine & beer. It was Friday so they also had bingo and really cool music. The staff is really nice... The atmosphere was really fun! We loved it! Will come back for sure!!!
Vkusnyi kofe, panini v samoe serdtse! Personal zamechatel'nyi! Vernus' snova! Spasibo rebiata!
I'm usually a breakfast muffin or scone guy, but had the blueberry and cream croissant this morning and it was awesome.  Wonderful, friendly staff!  I'll be back.

this place is amazing. the atmosphere is just so cozy and nice. the food is so good! The fruit in my parfait was fresh! the coffee is excellent as well. i definitely will be back! for my 3 items it was not pricey either, with a 20% tip i spent $25!  (the avocado toast was too good and i forgot to take a photo before taking a few bites...LOL!) I highly recommend Rendezbrew if you are looking for a good coffee spot!
We really enjoy this coffee shop and so much more, big part of the community.  we enjoy some of the fun events at night.  staff is friendly and food and drinks are great!
A great atmosphere & great coffee!

This cafe is adorable. They serve your basic coffee drinks to more complex. They have latte flights, hot cocoa flights and mojito flights. They serve beer and liquor, as well as food. Cute and fun place to hang with the family.
fun coffee, good atmosphere.
Great place to do remote work. People are super friendly.
Best chicken salad sandwich and wheat beer

This is my favorite coffee shop in the area, they always have music bingo on Friday nights my fiance Melody & I love going to.  The staff and the owners are really nice, and it's definitely a gem to the area to have a place like this!

I always enjoy coming here. The owners and staff are awesome. The atmosphere is amazing and relaxing. I know I can always come here to unwind and get a drink or pop in for coffee stop. Love this place

I absolutely LOVE this place. My friend and I arrive on a Sunday morning and we had a wonderful time. I love that they offer coffee flights, and the coffee was DELICIOUS. The bagels were homemade and definitely some of the best tasting bagels I've had in the area by far. I can't wait to go back for some of their sandwiches! The staff was super helpful and a complete joy.

Super clean and great service! Coolest vibe I've experienced yet in a coffee shop in Lancaster County! The woman who took my order helped me decide on what to get which I loved! She was right, it was yummy! Will be coming back a lot more often!

Today was my first time at Rendezbrew the service was great! Service was quick, staff was friendly and attentive. We purchased the coffee flight of the month and it was delish & the presentation was beautiful!! I will definitely be trying all of the monthly coffee flights from here on out! Thank you
Check them out. Best coffee and bagels anywhere but don't just take my word for it. Check them out for yourself, you won't be disappointed.
I went 2 days in a row for breakfast with my partner and we LOVE the coffee, fresh bagels and Croissants. Everything is fresh and super yummy.
Music bingo most Friday nights!
Great experience, clean place, good atmosphere and refined food. A place to come and stay for awhile.

THE BAGELS. Best bagels I have ever had. They are homemade and such a great price. I get the cheddar bagel with pesto cream cheese and its just my favorite . Lattes are usually pretty good! The shop is cute with lots of natural light too. I just love spending time in here and it doesn't get as crowded as CLT shops do. Love love love it.

I visited today for the first time and loved everything about my visit! The June latte flight was freaking amazing, and the avocado toast was out of this world! The atmosphere was spot on, and the girls working were super friendly and attentive.
Very nice place, owner very friendly would come back again!
Great place in Indian Land to grab a bite to eat.   Coffee is great, bagels and sandwiches are full of flavor and cooked perfectly.  Clean bathrooms and nice staff.  10/10.
I love this place. It is cozy, not too crowded.
Great little spot and great staff. Fun spot for a nice option for some different whiskeys the owner likes to try!

Great local place to get coffee or tea with a puffy bagel or breakfast sandwich.  They also have several local craft beers on tap and really good panini sandwiches and they do a fun music trivia night Fridays from 8-10.  Shannon and Skip are friendly owners and so is the staff.
Love this place can't wait to go back !! Bagels are a must try .

So glad this spot is here! It's quickly becoming a fav! Mimosas in the morning...divine fresh coffee options by day and great wine & beer options by night! Excellent customer service and attentive dog friendly owners. Way to wake up Indian Land  Make it your mission to drop in. Don't miss B-I-N-G-O night!

Very welcoming and pleasant place ! All staff was very helpful. Coffee is delicious! I was going to a birthday party and needed a hair tie after a crazy grocery shopping day ,  the weather was very windy.Clare was so nice and found one for me ) I felt like I came to get a cup of coffee to a friend's house.
Really really great cafe
Excellent coffee and atmosphere for relaxing. Shannon is a great hostess
Great atmosphere, great service, and great drinks! Prices are reasonable. I tried the white sangria, so good!
Wonderful little place.. The staff was kind.. good vibe... and the avocado toast was delicious... 1st time here will definitely be back...

Latte was ok.  Not bad or great.  I ordered a chocolate croissant.  The presentation was beautiful.  Unfortunately the crossiants was stale, not heated.  The chocolate tasted like Hershey's on top.  I took one bite and that was it.  When I handed the plate back I wasn't ask if the food was ok.
Omg so good!
The best place to be for casual conversation and friendship with the bonus of an excellent atmosphere along with great food and drink.  To also include wonderful friendly service.
Great service and busy place. Ten times better than any Starbucks
Very lively and friendly coffee house.
Great Ambience and good coffee. Will definitely be back to try the wine.
My favorite coffee shop
Bagels are fantastic the coffee is real the owner is very nice the place is exceptionally clean all good would definitely recommend
The very best
Tuesday night music bingo!
I love this place. It is a semi-quiet coffee shop will delicious food and drinks! I enjoy the ambiance and I do recommend coming here!! The service is also great!

It's a very lowkey and chill spot where you can order tea, coffee, alcohol and little small sandwiches like paninis. I just ordered a chicken panini and water. That sandwich was arguably the best sandwich I had ever eaten in my life. The bread was an immaculate balance between crunchy and soft. The cheese was melted very good that I could feel the ooey gooey-ness of it in my mouth. And the vegetables in the sandwich just blended right in with everything else and didn't taste like they were too much. Everything was just right and the sandwich was a pretty hefty size so you're not paying for a small sandwich. Very good!

Great spot to spend an evening.
Great coffee
Best lavender coffee in Charlotte (trust me, I've searched)! Recently moved from Charleston and have been missing this coffee staple in my life. Happy to have found this spot.
Great indoor and outdoor seating, friendly staff, treats for the kids and the grown ups.
Great atmosphere, plenty of seating (both indoor and outdoor), very friendly staff, and good food.
Nice coffee shop also serves alcohol as well. Start to get a nice crowd on the weekends around 10. Great place for a meeting up.

Yummy iced latte + paninis & lovely decor / interior! The avocado toast is BOMB! Loved the turkey caprese panini; it was a nice light sandwich but very tasty! It's a good price too, $8 for the sandwich and chips. (don't expect a huge chunk of mozzarella tho). I love all the plants and seating inside too! It's such a cute place!
Good coffee.
Best coffee around!

That's such a great place! Visited hundreds of times since live in the neighborhood and always was very satisfied! Recommend to my friends and now they are frequent visitors!
Food is delicious, place is nice and clean, great coffee! And what is the most important is that all the staff are extremely nice and friendly ! Always feel welcomed!
Thank you guys for all your work ! Really glad that my neighborhood got you there!
great food,atmoshere ,friendly employees,good prices and music bingo nite is the greatest !
Beautiful space with great coffee and an exceptional staff.
Best coffee in the area, very chill atmosphere, and the sweetest owners!
New to the area and stumbled upon this great place....just a cup of joe this morning, but I can see many return visits in the future....

Great coffee shop / bar.  Nice people and good drinks. They have  both indoor and outdoor seating.  Both were comfortable.  I had a glass of wine and sat on  the outdoor deck.  If you have a chance to make it here I would highly recommend.  They did a great job with this place.

First time here today and it was great! My kids did a class at The Magic Canvas next door, which I also recommend.

The staff was friendly and helpful, coffee was delicious, and nice atmosphere! Wish this was closer to my house because I would be a regular.
Great place. Good food. Good people. Nice vibe.

I purchased my first batch of the Jones Brew. As soon as I unboxed it, it smelled amazing.  I ground up some beans and made a pot the next morning. It was smooth and needed no milk, no sugar, nothing. It was great straight. Although, I can imagine a little Buffalo Trace Bourbon Cream in it on a cold fall morning in my future...
Coffee drinks are great. The space has a great design and feel. Perfect for bringing a book  or laptop to get some work done.
Awesome place to chill and work/chat. Amazing food and drinks!
Cool little place, beer, wine or coffee, your choice. Friendly staff.

Went for the first time today with a friend and had a fantastic experience. The girls working were so nice and helpful and the tea and panini were delicious. The atmosphere and vibe is really calming and inviting. I think I'll be a regular!
First time visitor but I'll definitely be back regularly. Great staff, casual atmosphere without unnecessary intrusive noise/music.  The hot and cold coffees were great.
Bagels and avocado toast were awesome and so is the coffee! Super fun atmosphere
A great selection of coffees & sandwiches. Chicken salad was fantastic.

My favorite spot near home. Best quality for coffee, food, and service. I come here at least once a week just because I miss the atmosphere and the people working there. Their menu has been expanding a lot lately. I especially recommend the avocado toast, yogurt parfait, and the sangria! Yum!
Cozy spot to get together with friends!

So today my 10 year old and I split the avocado toast with tomato and it was Amazing!!! Sooo good!!! The only thing I would encourage is gluten free toast as an option!!! (I have a few friends that want to try it but are gluten free!)
The staff here is so kind, and the owners are just the nicest people! The food's phenomenal (highly recommend their avocado toast) and their coffee is amazing. Absolutely a great place.
The coffee was good, food was good, and staff were friendly and helpful. The atmosphere of the place was great for lounging around. Will definitely be back!

This place is a gem! My husband and I met the owner Skip, nicest guy, great service, and delicious brews and coffee! Plus the name of the place is amazing. Will definitely come back here next time we are in Charlotte.
Cozy atmosphere, coffes,wine,beer,cheese platters,sandwhiches,overall great place to relax with friends.
Friendly staff and ambience is good. Food options are limited but what they serve is fresh and tasty. Hope they will introduce kids menu in future
Great atmosphere! Relaxing. Coffee bar is great! Establishment is very neat and tidy  Owners are very friendly and attentive. I'll be back!

5 stars easily. Great food, great drinks, great staff,  great atmosphere and great location. Planning on making this a regular "work from home" spot, a date night spot, a family outing spot. We absolutely loved it and will be back a lot!

This is the cutest coffee shop and wine bar! I love going here during the day for coffee and also coming here for date nights. The charcuterie board and sangria is the perfect combination! I'm so glad this spot opened in Indian land! It's amazing!
The owners were amazing; the paninis fresh and the made on the fly unsweetened tea was amazing!
First timer and loved it!  Cute little place with quaint and cindy seating.  Can't wait to use the patio too once the weather is permitting!
The bartender was awsome!!
Very nice place friendly staff loved the duo singing Courtney Lynn n Quinn
This place has an amazing vibe. Great Chia too! My husband and I will definitely be back to try the beer!
Great atmosphere, Great Coffee! My wife and I will definitely be back.
Great Service! Friendly Staff! Excellent coffee and atmosphere!

Really friendly staff, comfortable furniture with lots of different kinds of seating, great drinks and tasty menu, open late and open indoors! I loved all the plants and the wood table/counter tops. Definitely will come back again :)
Amazing place! love the environment and the owners, so sweet :))
The coffee was really good and the service was exquisite will be back again soon
Great Coffee and fantastic atmosphere. I love the decoration and the outdoor seating. I will give another go. Welcome to the neighborhood!
Great coffee, great food, great atmosphere, great people.
Nice atmosphere, good coffee and courteous employees.
We've already gotten coffees here a few times. Delicious drinks and a great atmosphere inside! Very happy to have Rendezbrew close by in Indian Land!
This place is so refreshing and bright! Then plants and high ceilings make it a really nice place to work or just hand out. The charcuterie board is so yummy.
Popped in for a post lunch pick me up. Friendly staff. Excellent latte. Quick service. Great place to study, have a meeting, or a moment to your self. Will be back very soon
I'm a black coffee drinker and picky at that...the Columbia coffee is excellent! It's the best coffee I have had South of Charlotte and even nicer to have good coffee in the neighborhood!
